{
  "texts": [
    "A client can request data from a connected peer, or the connected peer can initiate a data transfer.",
    "This data is segmented into chunks and streamed to the requesting peer, allowing real-time viewing of the data.",
    "The purpose of the latter is to submit large data files through the data channels and not congest or block the user interface.",
    "Different server methods specifically designed for managing various types of data stored on the server facilitate this process.",
    "On a two-way peer connection, a requestor peer asks for a requested peer for data, and uses Peer.js data channel to send data streams."
  ]
}